îóŸRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-05-05-twin0245.mdŸ@50a3138615aa736ec3b752b5e579725ce5ae8806537b77f7cfcdab489c2092eaπThis week in Nushell #245ëßNushell⁄*sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12769] updated 
``interprocess``
 to 2.0.1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12766] specified the required minimum 
``chrono``
 version
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12762] pinned 
``base64``
 to the fixed patch version
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12741] updated PLATFORM_SUPPORT regarding feature flags
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12740] avoided taking unnecessary ownership of intermediates
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12737] fixed 
``clippy::wrong_self_convention``
 in polars plugin
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12736] fixed new clippy lints
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12735] eliminated dead code in 
``nu-explore``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12688] updated the bundled readme in release archives
.
YizhePKU 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12761] fixed PWD not pointing to root paths
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12701] changed environment variables to be case-preserving
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12662] made path expansion no longer remove trailing slashes
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12603] migrated to a new PWD API
.
devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12760] fixed trailing slash in PWD set by 
``cd``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12729] upgraded to interprocess 2.0.0
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12728] flushed on every plugin 
``Data``
 message
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12727] added 
``toolkit release-pkg windows``
 for Windows release pkg builds
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12714] fixed Windows Terminal profile installation
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12710] bumped version to 
``0.93.1``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12709] bumped version to 
``0.93.0``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12708] bumped 
``reedline``
 to 
``0.32.0``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12698] fixed missing local socket feature
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12685] made 
``bytes build``
 accept integer values as individual bytes
.
ExaltedBagel 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12759] enabled columns with spaces for into_sqlite by adding quotes to column names
.
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12757] bumped 
``base64``
 to 0.22.1
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12756] refactored flattening to reduce intermediate allocations
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12752] fixed a typo
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12742] removed some macros
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12702] added 
``fs``
 feature to 
``nix``
 dependency
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12682] removed lazy records
, and provided a 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12524] ``ListStream``
 touchup
.
szepeviktor 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12751] minimized future false positive typos
.
rgwood 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12692] made some changes to 
``explore``
: adopted 
``anyhow``
, supported 
``CustomValue``
, removed help system
.
hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12721] upgraded Nu to v0.93.0 for nightly and release workflow
.
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12720] changed wix install method from perMachine to perUser
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12694] fixed a rust-analyzer warning
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12693] restored 
``query web --as-table``
 to working order
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12629] overhauled shell_integration to enable individual control over ansi escape sequences
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/9956] added raw-string literal support
.
maxim-uvarov 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12719] added more tests to the 
``polars``
 plugin
.
amtoine 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12718] added support for cell-paths to NUON
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12717] improved NUON documentation
.
FilipAndersson245 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12469] initiated Tango migration
.
lavafroth 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12438] fixed a bug to prevent relative directory traversal from crashing
.
merelymyself 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12412] prevented 
``each``
 from swallowing errors when 
``eval_block``
 returns a 
``ListStream``
.
rtpg 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12033] reported errors that occur on file operations in ls
.
